ind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majoduwlapu Alxaloqi","text_ar":"مَجْدُولَةُ الخَلْقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A girl,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young woman, goodly in respect of compacture; well compacted in respect of make"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O.) ―         -b3-  And (assumed tropical:)  A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slender,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or an"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elegant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"sword. (K.) ―         -b4-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hungry, having his belly bound round:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or [simply]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hungry;"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the dial. of Hudheyl: (S, O:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very hungry:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose bowels are almost dried up by hunger:"},{"kind":"text","text":"an epithet said to be applied to a hungry man because he binds round his belly with a stone [within the bandage] on account of his hunger: it is said to have been the custom of any hungry man, among the Arabs, to bind his belly with a bandage, under which he sometimes put a stone. (TA.) ―         -b5-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A letter"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kitaAbN","text_ar":"كِتَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"); thus called because bound round with a thread, or string: so in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"warada EalaY~a","text_ar":"وَرَدَ عَلَىَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoSuwbN","text_ar":"مَعْصُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A letter came to me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","A","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}